# Project Standards
- All Python code must include type hints
- Never remove existing type hints or docstrings
- Use snake_case for functions, PascalCase for classes
- Quality tools (ruff, mypy, pytest, mutmut) are enforced via pre-commit — do NOT run them during coding iterations
- Remind user to run quality checks only before git push, not during AI-assisted development